General Khalifa Haftar's forces have been besieging the city since April 2019. But intensified military support from Turkey helped government forces drive General Haftar's Russian-backed troops back from the frontlines. A new diplomatic effort is under way to try to restart talks on a lasting ceasefire in the oil-rich nation. The recapture of the international airport in Tripoli - long out of use - is the strongest symbolic victory for the Libyan government so far, reports the BBC's Arab affairs editor Sebastian Usher. Libya has been torn by violence since long-time ruler Col Muammar Gaddafi was deposed and killed in 2011 by Nato-backed forces. --BBC--